\DP

fr:mainmatter.html:p:
By continuing this with a step of 
eg I, we could discharge the assumption of q and arrive at a proof in NM of 
eg (p \land q), p \;/\; 
eg q. Or we could discharge the assumption of p and arrive at a proof in NM of 
eg (p \land q), q \;/\; 
eg p. But either way, we'd still be left with one of p or q as an open assumption, and no obvious strategy for getting to a proof of 
eg (p \land q) \;/\; 
eg p \lor 
eg q.

